{
  "stem": "1537.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 2.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So only my father, my mother, my sister, Zippora, who lives in [NON-ENGLISH], my brother Jacob was in the labor camp, already in Russia, you know?",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my brother, David, also, we'd never heard about-- from him.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my sister, Toby-- she was eight or nine years old.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And my brother Joseph Betzalel, and me, and my sister's little boy, maybe two-and-a-half, three years old.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "See, always, one child was in our place for a year to give a break for my sister, because she had three children.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she had to take care of the business.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "In the [INAUDIBLE], that's very, very, very hard for her.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So in order to give her a break, that's what we used to go.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then we couldn't bring back the child anymore to my sister, because the Jew were not supposed to travel.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So that's he way the child ended up with us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And that's the way they took the little boy, also with us, to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "From the ghetto?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The only thing I can tell you by weeks.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Approximately, I think, the 15 of April, approximately, they took us to the ghetto, right away, the next day after Passover.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I know, we were approximately two or three weeks in the ghetto, because we were the first transport.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They took us to Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "So but I didn't know that we are-- where they're going to take us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We thought they are taking us somewhere, where-- because the Germans, they don't trust us, the Jews, because we are against the Germans, obviously-- so we thought they're going to take us somewhere to be away.",
      "word_count": 36
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "You're not to be spies for the Allies.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "You know, that's what we thought.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The day?",
      "word_count": 2
    }
  ],
